# WebCamera Stream
*In this example we will stream the data from your connected web-camera or any other camera-like device and perform real-time data processing*

How to take a photo in WL?

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
# WebCamera Stream
*In this example we will stream the data from your connected web-camera or any other camera-like device and perform real-time data processing*

How to take a photo in WL?

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
CurrentImage[]

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
(*VB[*)(FrontEndRef["00464a90-c955-4c55-8dfe-5f22dfb89cbd"])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNkYGAoZgESHvk5KRCeEJBwK8rPK3HNS3GtSE0uLUlMykkNVgEKGxiYmJkkWhroJluamuqaJAMJi5S0VF3TNCOjlLQkC8vkpBQAedAV3g=="*)(*]VB*)

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: true
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
.md
However, there is a better way if you need to stream the data from a camera __continuously__:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
However, there is a better way if you need to stream the data from a camera __continuously__:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
cam = DeviceOpen["Camera"]
cam["FrameRate"] = 30;

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
RefreshRate[cur = DeviceRead[cam], 1/30.0]

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: true
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
.md
This should go without any lag. If your device support `60`, change the code accordingly. 

:::note
`Refresh` will not force Wolfram Kernel to work faster, than it can deliver even if you set *1/100.0* update interval.
:::

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
This should go without any lag. If your device support `60`, change the code accordingly. 

:::note
`Refresh` will not force Wolfram Kernel to work faster, than it can deliver even if you set *1/100.0* update interval.
:::

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: true
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
.md
## Basic data-processing
Let's try binarize our images

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
## Basic data-processing
Let's try binarize our images

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Refresh[cur = DeviceRead[cam] // Binarize, 1/30.0]

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: true
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
.md
One could also try applying neural network processing, for instance, to identify faces. There is a built-in function for it in Wolfram Language Standard Library:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
One could also try applying neural network processing, for instance, to identify faces. There is a built-in function for it in Wolfram Language Standard Library:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
cur // FindFaces 

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
{Rectangle[{190.5`,244.5`},{310.5`,397.5`}]}

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
HighlightImage[cur, {Green, Opacity[0.3], %}]

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
(*VB[*)(FrontEndRef["d667025f-ba56-4807-ae23-8a12a3dc386b"])(*,*)(*"1:eJxTTMoPSmNkYGAoZgESHvk5KRCeEJBwK8rPK3HNS3GtSE0uLUlMykkNVgEKp5iZmRsYmabpJiWamumaWBiY6yamGhnrWiQaGiUapyQbW5glAQB9axVt"*)(*]VB*)

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: true
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
.md
Let's apply this in real-time:

*Make sure to stop other widgets by cleaning the output cells*

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Let's apply this in real-time:

*Make sure to stop other widgets by cleaning the output cells*

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Refresh[HighlightImage[cur = DeviceRead[cam], With[{
  faces = FindFaces[cur]
}, 
  {Opacity[0.3], Green, If[Length[faces] > 0, First[faces], Rectangle[{0,0}, {0,0}]]}
]], 1/30.0]

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: true
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
.md
## Image Displacement
Firstly try to compute the difference between the images:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
## Image Displacement
Firstly try to compute the difference between the images:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
cam = DeviceOpen["Camera"];
cam["FrameRate"] = 30;

Refresh[DeviceRead[cam]-DeviceRead[cam], 0.1]

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: true
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
.md
A more sophisticated optical flow method returns a vector field of the horizontal and vertical displacement:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
A more sophisticated optical flow method returns a vector field of the horizontal and vertical displacement:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Refresh[Module[{
  flow = ImageDisplacements[{DeviceRead[cam], DeviceRead[cam]}]
},
  Image[Rescale[flow[[1]]]]
], 0.1]

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Props:
  Hidden: true
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
.md
__Rotation component__ composed on top of the image:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Display: markdown
Type: Output
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
__Rotation component__ composed on top of the image:

%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Type: Input
%-------------------------------------------------------------------------%
Refresh[Module[{
  flow,
  listCurl, curl, frame
},

flow = ImageDisplacements[{frame = DeviceRead[cam], DeviceRead[cam]}][[1]];

(* Extract the rotation component of the flow by computing its curl: *)

listCurl =
  flow |-> 
   ListConvolve[{{0.5, 0, -0.5}}, flow[[All, All, 2]], {{1, 2}, {1, 2}},
      "Fixed"] - 
    ListConvolve[{{-0.5}, {0}, {0.5}}, 
     flow[[All, All, 1]], {{1, 2}, {1, 2}}, "Fixed"];
     
curl = ImageAdjust@Image@GaussianFilter[listCurl@flow, 8 {3, 1}];

(* Colorize the rotation map and superimpose it on top of the original image: *)

ImageCompose[frame, 
 SetAlphaChannel[
  Colorize[curl, 
   ColorFunction -> ColorData[{"TemperatureMap", "Reverse"}]], 
  ColorNegate[curl]]]
  
], 1/10.0]

